AWS Infrastructure Setup
Step 1: VPC & Networking
Option A: Use Default VPC (Easier)

AWS provides a default VPC in each region
Has public subnets across multiple AZs
✅ Recommended for learning
Option B: Create Custom VPC (Production-like)

Bash

# Using AWS CLI (optional)
aws ec2 create-vpc --cidr-block 10.0.0.0/16 --tag-specifications 'ResourceType=vpc,Tags=[{Key=Name,Value=fullstack-vpc}]'
Manual Steps (AWS Console):

VPC Dashboard → Create VPC

Name: fullstack-vpc
CIDR: 10.0.0.0/16
Create Subnets (2 public subnets in different AZs)

Name	AZ	CIDR
public-subnet-1a	us-east-1a	10.0.1.0/24
public-subnet-1b	us-east-1b	10.0.2.0/24
Internet Gateway

Create IGW → Attach to VPC
Route Table

Create route: 0.0.0.0/0 → Internet Gateway
Associate with both public subnets
Step 2: Security Groups
Create 3 security groups:

SG-1: Frontend-SG
text

Inbound Rules:
- HTTP (80) from 0.0.0.0/0
- HTTPS (443) from 0.0.0.0/0 (optional)
- SSH (22) from YOUR_IP (for debugging)

Outbound Rules:
- All traffic
SG-2: ALB-SG
text

Inbound Rules:
- HTTP (80) from 0.0.0.0/0
- HTTPS (443) from 0.0.0.0/0 (optional)

Outbound Rules:
- All traffic
SG-3: Backend-SG
text

Inbound Rules:
- Custom TCP (3000) from ALB-SG (use security group ID reference!)
- SSH (22) from YOUR_IP (optional, for debugging)

Outbound Rules:
- All traffic
AWS Console Steps:

EC2 → Security Groups → Create security group
For Backend-SG inbound rule:
Type: Custom TCP
Port: 3000
Source: Custom → Select ALB-SG from dropdown
Step 3: Create IAM Role for EC2 (Optional but Recommended)
text

Role Name: EC2-FullStack-Role
Trusted Entity: EC2
Policies:
- AmazonSSMManagedInstanceCore (for Systems Manager Session Manager)
- CloudWatchAgentServerPolicy (for logs)
